<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 2:04AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Beaver
and northeastern Texas Counties through 245 AM CDT...
At 204 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles northeast of Hough, or 13 miles south of Feterita, moving east
at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Hooker, Tyrone, Turpin, Hough and Baker.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
